Quote:  FRIGATE MACKEREL <i>Auxis thazard</i>(Lacepede) ... This beautifully-shaped fish is known in Australia as the Frigate Mackerel. Fishermen there also call it Leadenall from the appearance of polished lead it presents when freshly caught.
